The paper discusses the use of human demonstrations to improve data efficiency in reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The dataset collected and described in the paper consists of replays from Atari 2600 games, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also mentions possible research directions related to robotics (cs.RO), which could involve using the dataset to train robots to perform tasks in the real world.
